  "commentary": "**DEALER HEDGING COMMENTARY:**\n\nWith SPX at 7138.53 sitting just below the massive +11.1B gamma wall at 7150, dealers are positioned to aggressively sell any push higher into that strike, creating significant resistance. The PIN regime with 116.6B total GEX confirms dealers will provide liquidity against directional moves - selling rallies toward 7150-7200 and buying any dips toward 7100. Key inflection points are the 7150 max gamma strike above and the 7100 support wall below, with the market likely to chop between these levels given the stabilizing gamma profile.\n\n**Bottom line:** expect sideways grinding with strong resistance at 7150 and support around 7100.",
